\subsection{Minimal polynomial}
\begin{definition}\label{nf.minimal_polynomial}
\uses{nf}
The **minimal polynomial** of an element \(a\) in a {{ KNOWL('nf', 'number field') }} \(K\) is the unique monic polynomial \(f(X)\in\Q[X]\) of minimal degree such that \(f(a)=0\). It is necessarily irreducible over $\Q.$
\end{definition}


